Integration test suite for ctx-scan, exercising `walk_dir`, `hash::compute/store`, `check_run`, `update_run`, and `runner::summarize` both hermetically (in-memory) and against the real filesystem in OS tmpdirs. It's the executable spec for how staleness detection, ignore-file semantics, and scope gating are supposed to behave — an editor changing behavior in `runner.rs`, `walker.rs`, or `hash.rs` should expect these tests to catch drift.

Two fake implementations back the hermetic half: `FakeFs` (an in-memory `BTreeMap<String,String>` implementing `ctx_summarize::fs::Fs`, with `with_source()` seeding `prompts/summarizer-{leaf,rollup}.md` plus `src/lib.rs`, and `prompts_only()` seeding just prompts) and `RecordingAgent` (implements `ctx_summarize::agent::Agent::complete`, records every `(system, user)` call and always returns `format!("SUMMARY[{system}]")`, never erroring). Anything asserting on agent call counts relies on `RecordingAgent` never failing — it's not a fault-injection double.

Filesystem-backed tests use `test_dir(label) -> PathBuf` (a fixed path under `std::env::temp_dir()` per label, not per-run-unique) and always `drop(std::fs::remove_dir_all(&base))` both before and after, so tests are not safely parallel-clean if a previous run crashed mid-test without cleanup — a leftover dir from an aborted run could leak into the next run's fixture. `prompts_path()` resolves prompts via `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR` rather than relying on cwd, since production code loads prompts relative to the process's cwd but tests need an absolute path independent of where `cargo test` is invoked from.

Key behavioral facts pinned by these tests (coupling to `walker.rs`/`hash.rs`/`runner.rs` internals):
- `walk_dir` always excludes `.context/` and binary-looking files (e.g. `.png`), and applies a built-in default ignore for `target/`.
- `.ctxignore` is seeded from `.gitignore` **once**, on first `walk_dir` contact with a directory lacking `.ctxignore`; after seeding, `.gitignore` is never consulted again — a test explicitly grows `.gitignore` post-seed and asserts no effect (`walk_seeds_ctxignore_from_gitignore_once_then_decouples`).
- `check_run` reports the root directory as stale via the empty string `""` in `stale_dirs`, not a path like `"."`.
- Editing one file marks exactly that file's leaf and its ancestor directory rollups stale, not the whole tree (`stale_dirs == ["src", ""]` for `src/main.rs`).
- `update_run` regenerates only what's stale: one leaf edit triggers exactly 3 agent calls (leaf + parent rollup + root rollup); a no-op second run makes zero agent calls.
- Deleting a source file causes the next `update_run` to report it in `orphan_leaves` and physically remove the stale `.ctx` file.
- `runner::MAX_TARGETS` is the scope-gate threshold; `summarize(..., approved: bool)`'s last bool param bypasses `ScopeTooLarge` when `true`.

Depends on `ctx_summarize` (`agent::Agent`, `error::SummError`, `fs::{Fs, StdFs}`, `runner::load_prompts`) as well as `ctx_scan`'s own `error`, `hash`, `runner`, `walker` modules — this file is as much a contract test between the two crates as it is a unit test of `ctx-scan`.